# Neighborhood Golf Carts — Business Brain

This workspace is the **Neighborhood Golf Carts (NGC) Business Brain**. Before answering business questions, read relevant files in `knowledge/`.

## Start here

- Index: `knowledge/00_index.md`
- Company: `knowledge/01_company/profile.md`
- Lithium products: `knowledge/02_products/lithium_conversions.md`
- Services & policies: `knowledge/03_services/shop_services.md`
- Legacy/discontinued: `knowledge/archive/legacy_mobile.md`

## Current business facts (quick reference)

- **Shop-only** repair & lithium conversions — **no mobile service**, no trip charges
- **Address:** 71363 Thelma Ln, Suite E, Covington, LA 70433
- **Phone:** 985-402-1206 | **Email:** contact@ngcgolfcarts.com
- **Hours:** Mon–Fri 8 AM – 5 PM
- **Lithium:** Professional Kits only (36V/48V/MINI/72V/150AH) — NGC Conversion line discontinued
- **Warranty:** 5 years battery + BMS
- **Diagnostic:** $179 minimum — not waived; applies toward repair on known-issue jobs
- **Pickup/delivery:** Free within 40 mi of North Shore shop **or** anywhere on South Shore of Lake Pontchartrain; **$99** outside that free zone
- **No cart sales or rentals** yet
- **Intake:** [SOP-01](knowledge/04_operations/sops/SOP-01_customer_intake.md) — one lead text, one 24h follow-up then stop; photo standards; diag $179 + tax

## Authority order

1. Owner/staff statements in conversation (most recent)
2. `knowledge/` files
3. `external_docs/exports/` (pricebook CSV, QBO exports)
4. `external_docs/My Drive/` documents — check `knowledge/archive/legacy_mobile.md` for outdated items

## Never do

- Quote **mobile service**, **trip charges**, or **NGC Conversion** lithium products
- Invent prices — use `knowledge/03_services/pricebook_reference.md` or the CSV export
- Include **customer PII**, **passwords**, or **bank account numbers** in responses or new files
- Treat Google `.gsheet` / `.gdoc` stub files as readable content

## Tone

- **Customers:** Friendly, professional, plain language — like a knowledgeable shop advisor
- **Staff:** Direct, procedural, reference SOPs and checklists when relevant

